  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Individuals 1460 days-old or older (approximately 4 years old)",
    "One or more prescriptions of asthma related medications",
    "Two or more relevant ICD9 codes in two or more in-person visits, on separate calendar days",
    "Atopic stratification: ICD9 code 493.0 or two or more allergy-related ICD9 codes on separate calendar days",
    "Smoking history (packs/day x years) captured where available (not inclusion/exclusion criterion)"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "The asthma phenotype algorithm identifies cases as individuals 4+ years old with both: (1) one or more asthma medication prescriptions AND (2) two or more asthma ICD9 codes (493.x) from separate in-person visits on different calendar days. Cases are excluded if they have any of the specified exclusionary conditions (cystic fibrosis, COPD, transplant-related codes, etc.). Controls are individuals 4+ years old with no asthma diagnoses, no asthma medications, and no exclusionary conditions. Cases can be stratified by atopic status based on presence of allergic asthma (493.0) or multiple allergy-related diagnoses. The algorithm includes extensive medication lists categorized by severity (mild, moderate, severe) and comprehensive exclusion criteria to ensure phenotype specificity.",
